=[[OpenBionics Hands]]=

[https://openbionics.org/ OpenΒionics] is an open-source initiative for the development of affordable, light-weight, modular, adaptive robot hands and prosthetic devices, that can be easily reproduced using off-the-shelf materials. Our robot hands cost less than 100$ and weigh less than 200 gr while our new anthropomorphic prosthetic hands cost less than 200$ and weigh less than 300 gr.

=Other Examples=

* [[AbilityMate]], a company that supports people with disabilities to design and manufacture their own prosthetics and assistive devices,
* [[Wikihouse]],  a  foundation  which  supports  people  to  design  and  build  sustainable housing,
* [[RepRap]],  an  open  source  organization  that  designs  3D  printers  designed  to  replicate themselves,
* [[OSvehicle]], a company that supports the open source manufacture of vehicles.

